a Ritter]], American actress and singer (d. 1969) *[[1907]] &ndash; [[Johnny Longden]], English-American jockey and trainer (d. 2003) *[[1911]] &ndash; [[Willem Johan Kolff]], Dutch physician and inventor (d. 2009) *[[1912]] &ndash; [[Tibor Sekelj]], Hungarian lawyer, explorer, and author (d. 1988) *[[1913]] &ndash; [[Mel Allen]], American sportscaster (d. 1996) * 1913 &ndash; [[Woody Hayes]], American football player and coach (d. 1987) * 1913 &ndash; [[Jimmy Hoffa]], American trade union leader (d. 1975) * 1913 &ndash; [[James Pike]], American bishop (d. 1969) *[[1916]] &ndash; [[Marcel Bigeard]], French general (d. 2010) * 1916 &ndash; [[Sally Gray]], English actress and singer (d. 2006) * 1916 &ndash; [[Masaki Kobayashi]], Japanese director and producer (d. 1996) * 1916 &ndash; [[Edward Platt]], American actor (d. 1974) *[[1917]] &ndash; [[Herbert A. Hauptman]], American mathematician and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 2011) *[[1921]] &ndash; [[Hugh Downs]], American journalist, game show host, and producer * 1921 &ndash; [[Hazel McCallion]], Canadian businesswoman and politician, 3rd [[Mayor of Mississauga]] *[[1923]] &ndash; [[Jay Hebert]], American golfer (d. 1997) *[[1924]] &ndash; [[Patricia Knatchbull, 2nd Countess Mountbatten of Burma]] (d. 2017) *[[1927]] &ndash; [[Lois Maxwell]], Canadian-Australian model and actress (d. 2007) *[[1928]] &ndash; [[William Allain]], American soldier and politician, 58th [[Governor of Mississippi]] (d. 2013) * 1928 &ndash; [[Vicente T. Blaz]], American general and politician (d. 2014) *[[1929]] &ndash; [[Vic Morrow]], American actor and director (d. 1982) *[[1931]] &ndash; [[Bernie Geoffrion]], Canadian-American ice hockey player and coach (d. 2006) * 1931 &ndash; [[Brian Kelly (actor)|Brian Kelly]], American actor and director (d. 2005) *[[1932]] &ndash; [[Harriet Andersson]], Swedish actress *[[1934]] &ndash; [[Florence Henderson]], American actress and singer (d. 2016) *[[1935]] &ndash; 