{{Use British English|date=November 2013}}
{{third-party|date=June 2012}}
The '''Fuzz Club''' was an [[indie (music)|indie]] rock night hosted by [[University of Sheffield Union of Students]], which ran from 1999 to 2009. It claimed to be the biggest students union rock night in the UK outside [[London]]. 

The night ran weekly on Thursdays throughout termtime and hosts new bands; sometimes local, sometimes national. The club provided a variety of music from heavy rock in the ''Bleach'' room to [[indie (music)|indie]] in the main fuzz room.

Fuzz Club was part of the circuit for new bands trying to make a name for themselves. In recent years, it had hosted [[Keane (band)|Keane]], [[The Long Blondes]], [[Editors (band)|Editors]], [[The Zutons]], [[The Killers]], [[Bloc Party]], [[The xx]], [[La Roux]], [[Future of the Left]], [[British Sea Power]], [[65daysofstatic]], [[Ida Maria]], [[Hot Chip]], [[Florence and the Machine]] and [[The Others (band)|The Others]].

The club night ran since 1999 and initially alternated with ''Bleach'', a heavier rock night, which instead became resident in the Fuzz Club's second room - essentially part of Fuzz Club.

At the end of the academic year 2008/09, the Fuzz Club is ended, with the last night held on 11 June 2009.  The night has now been replaced with Live Wire, opening 23 September 2010.

