{{Infobox song contest | name = Melodifestivalen | year = 1973 | theme = | logo = | final = 10 February 1973 | presenters = [[Alicia Lundberg]] | winner = "[[You're Summer|Sommaren som aldrig säger nej]]" by Malta | vote = Regional juries | host = | venue = [[Sveriges Television|SVT]] Television Centre, [[Stockholm]] | entries = | interval = | opening = }}
'''[[Melodifestivalen]] 1973''' was the selection for the 14th song to represent [[Sweden]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. It was the 13th time that this system of picking a song had been used. 10 songwriters were selected by [[Sveriges Television|SVT]] for the competition. The final was broadcast on [[SVT1|TV1]] but was not broadcast on radio.
The third place act, Agnetha, Anni-Frid, Björn & Benny, returned to take part in Melodifestivalen 1974 under their new moniker [[ABBA]].
This year (1973) was completely erased from the Swedish archives.
