{{unreferenced|date=March 2012}} {{Infobox book|<!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> |name=My Sister, My Love |title_orig= |translator= |image= My sister my love.jpg |caption= First edition cover design |author=[[Joyce Carol Oates]] |illustrator= |cover_artist= |country=United States |language=English |series= |genre=Novel |publisher=[[Ecco Press]] |release_date=24 June 2008 |english_release_date= |media_type=Print (hardback) |pages=576pp (first edition, hardback) | isbn = 0061547484 | isbn_note = (first edition, hardback) | dewey= 813/.54 22 | congress= PS3565.A8 M895 2008 | oclc= 212893540 |preceded_by=[[The Gravedigger's Daughter]] |}}
'''''My Sister, My Love''''' is a 2008 novel by [[Joyce Carol Oates]], her 37th published novel. It reimagines the [[Death of JonBenét Ramsey|JonBenét Ramsey]] murder, with the ice-skating champion Bliss Rampike standing in for JonBenét, and is narrated by her surviving older brother, Skyler Rampike.
The book received generally positive reviews, with ''[[USA Today]]'' noting, "Employing her powerful imagination, the gifted Oates gets inside her fictional characters’ tormented souls to solve the case…as a literary exercise, it deserves a rave…she brilliantly depicts status-obsessed parents who alternately push and ignore their deeply unhappy children."
{{Joyce Carol Oates}}
