{{EngvarB|date=September 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox newspaper | name = National Network | logo = National_Network_News.png | image = | caption = | type = Weekly [[newspaper]] | format = Tabloid | owners = [[Jerry Needam]] | founder = | publisher = Network Printing and Publishing Company | president = | editor = | chiefeditor = Chris Konkwo | depeditor = | assoceditor = G. K. Girigiri | maneditor = | generalmanager = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | metroeditor = | metrochief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = Ken Asinobi | photoeditor = | staff = | foundation = {{Start date|df=yes|2004|11|25}} | political = | language = English | ceased publication = | relaunched = | headquarters = No 6 Udi Street, [[Diobu, Port Harcourt|Diobu]], [[Rivers State]] | circulation = | circulation_date = | sister newspapers = | ISSN = | oclc = | RNI = | website = {{URL|http://www.nationalnetworkonline.com}} | free = | dirinteractive = | publishing_country = Nigeria | publishing_city = [[Port Harcourt]] }}
The '''''National Network''''' is an [[English language]] [[List of Nigerian newspapers|Nigerian weekly newspaper]] founded 25 November 2004.<ref name="national">{{cite web|url=http://itvradionigeria.com/news/nigerian-media/nigerian-newspapers-2/|title=Nigerian Newspapers|work=Itvradionigeria.com|publisher=Independent Television and Radio|date= |accessdate=20 June 2014}}</ref> It is published by Network Printing and Publishing Company and has its headquarters in the [[Diobu, Port Harcourt|Diobu]] area of [[Port Harcourt]], [[Rivers State]]. Topics the newspaper covers include local and national main news, sports, business, political events and personalities.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.nationalnetworkonline.com/contact.html|title=National Network Newspapers- Contact Information| publisher=''Nationalnetworkonline.com''|date= |accessdate=19 June 2014}}</ref>
In January 2005, [[Jerry Needam]], owner of the paper was arrested at his office for allegedly fabricating a news report aimed at tarnishing [[Rivers State Police]] commissioner Sylvester Araba's image and reputation.<ref name="media arrests">{{cite web|url=http://afrol.com/articles/15399|title=New media-related arrests in Nigeria|publisher=Afrol News|date=27 January 2005|accessdate=22 June 2014}}</ref>
In 2011, ''National Network'' celebrated the "seventh" anniversary of its foundation. The ceremony which took place at the Silverbird Hall, Port Harcourt, was the most attended of its kind in the state's history. Individual awards were also presented to prominent citizens deemed to have excelled to the highest degree in their chosen fields.<ref name="anniversary">{{cite web| url=http://www.modernghana.com/news/364688/1/seventh-year-anniversary-celebration-national-netw.html|title=Seventh Year Anniversary Celebration National Network Makes History|publisher=ModernGhana.com|last=Kwaaba|first=Frank|date=2 December 2011|accessdate=19 June 2014}}</ref><ref name="wike">{{cite news|url=http://www.punchng.com/news/wike-amaechi-trade-blames-over-rivers-crisis/|title=Wike, Amaechi trade blames over Rivers crisis|publisher=Punchng.com|last=Utebor|first=Simon|date=22 December 2013|accessdate=19 June 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131222140207/http://www.punchng.com/news/wike-amaechi-trade-blames-over-rivers-crisis/|archivedate=22 December 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
