[[Image:SaintStupid.jpg|thumb|250px|At the annual Saint Stupid's Day Parade on April 1, 2001]]
The '''Saint Stupid's Day Parade''' is an annual parade in [[San Francisco]] on April 1.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://sf.funcheap.com/st-stupids-day-parade-san-francisco/|title=39th Annual “St. Stupid’s Day” Parade {{!}} SF|work=FunCheapSF.com|access-date=2017-11-08|language=en-US}}</ref> It was founded by [[Bishop Joey|Ed Holmes]] (Bishop Joey of the First Church of the Last Laugh<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/04/02/st-stupids-day-parade_n_1397985.html|title=St. Stupid's Day Parade Marches Through April Fool's Day In San Francisco (PHOTOS)|last=Medina|first=Sarah|date=2012-04-02|work=Huffington Post|access-date=2017-11-08|language=en-US}}</ref>) in the late 1970s with the understanding that one of the unifying bonds in society is stupidity. If April 1 falls on a weekday, the parade starts at the foot of Market Street and follows a route through the financial district. If April 1 falls on a weekend, the parade starts at the [[Transamerica Pyramid]], proceeds up Columbus Avenue and ends at [[Washington Square (San Francisco)|Washington Square]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://keepincalendar.com/April-1/Saint%20Stupid's%20Day%20Parade%20(St.%20Stupid%20Day)/455|title=Saint Stupid's Day Parade (St. Stupid Day) {{!}} April 1|last=good2create|work=KeepIn Calendar|access-date=2017-11-08|language=en-US}}</ref> The parade begins at noon.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/weird/Saint-Stupids-Day-San-Francisco-Celebrates-St-Stupids-Day-Parade-253475241.html|title=San Francisco Celebrates St. Stupid’s Day|work=NBC Bay Area|access-date=2017-11-08|language=en}}</ref> The parade includes free lunch, confetti, flags and costumes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/04/02/st-stupids-day-parade_n_1397985.html|title=St. Stupid's Day Parade Marches Through April Fool's Day In San Francisco (PHOTOS)|last=Medina|first=Sarah|date=2012-04-02|work=Huffington Post|access-date=2017-11-08|language=en-US}}</ref>
